💁🏾‍♀️ HD lace, short for High Definition lace

Premium, ultra fine lace material originally developed for use in film and television. It’s made to be virtually invisible on camera, which is exactly why it’s become the industry standard for creating undetectable hairlines.

💁🏾‍♀️ What Makes HD Lace Superior?

Lace Fibre Composition:
HD lace is made from ultra thin polyamide fibres woven into a fine mesh. This material is designed to be sheer, lightweight, and breathable, allowing it to conform seamlessly to all skin tones without the need for heavy foundation or tinting.

✅ Thinking of upgrading your lace?

Investing in high quality HD lace is not a luxury, it’s a standard for clean, confident installs. If you want your wig to look like it’s growing out of your scalp HD is the way forward.

Our client wanted something that required less maintenance than her prior red tones do due to the consistent fade that comes with it. Do you know why red fades? .
.
The red hair molecule is larger & heavier than other colour molecules so it has difficulty in penetrating the cortex of the hair as deeply as the other colour molecules. As it isn’t as deep it sits on the surface of the hair shaft so when you wash your hair the warmth of the water swells the cuticle and makes the red dye molecules loose and prone to being washed away more easily
.
.
